HEADWORD: Seraphim
<hw>Ser"a*phim</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The Hebrew plural
of <er>Seraph</er>. Cf. <er>Cherubim</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The double plural form <xex>seraphims</xex> is sometimes
used, as in the King James version of the Bible, <au>Isa. vi. 2 and
6.</au></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

